Sentencas: The microstructure and local chemistry of the interface between the screen-printed La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3 (LSCF) thin film cathode and Gd-doped ceria (GDC) electrolyte substrate have been investigated.
Titulo: Mutual Diffusion Occurring at the Interface between La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3 Cathode and Gd-doped Ceria Electrolyte during IT-SOFC Cell Preparation

Sentencas: Elemental distribution analyses, by energy-dispersive X-ray spectroscopy operated in scanning transmission electron microscopy (STEM) mode, illustrate that all constituent elements in GDC and LSCF mutually diffuse across the LSCF/GDC interface, with equal diffusion length.
Titulo: Mutual Diffusion Occurring at the Interface between La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3 Cathode and Gd-doped Ceria Electrolyte during IT-SOFC Cell Preparation

Sentencas: This leads to the formation of mutual diffusion zones at the LSCF/GDC interfaces, with the resultant mixture of diffusing ions being associated with specific valence state changes, as verified by STEM electron energy loss spectroscopy analyses.
Titulo: Mutual Diffusion Occurring at the Interface between La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3 Cathode and Gd-doped Ceria Electrolyte during IT-SOFC Cell Preparation

Sentencas: Moreover, this mutual diffusion can result in microstructural changes, where superstructure formation is accompanied by enhancement of oxygen vacancy ordering at this region.
Titulo: Mutual Diffusion Occurring at the Interface between La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3 Cathode and Gd-doped Ceria Electrolyte during IT-SOFC Cell Preparation

Sentencas: Such mutual diffusion and associated microstructure evolution is considered to be detrimental to fuel cell efficiency and should be suppressed by lowering cell fabrication temperatures.
Titulo: Mutual Diffusion Occurring at the Interface between La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3 Cathode and Gd-doped Ceria Electrolyte during IT-SOFC Cell Preparation
